Chukwudi Akasike, Port Harcourt The Rivers State Government has confirmed its second case of the coronavirus. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control had on Monday listed Rivers among the states where fresh cases of coronavirus had been confirmed. Speaking with newsmen in Port Harcourt on Tuesday, the Commissioner for Health, Prof. Princewill Chike, described the new patient as a 63-year-old retiree, who spent about a month in the United Kingdom, before returning to Nigeria on March 20, 2020 via the Lagos International Airport. Chike said, “He has been moved to the state treatment centre and he is receiving treatment in line with established treatment guidelines for his general condition. “Contact tracing has commenced and samples are being collected from high risk contacts for reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction analysis. Risk communication and community engagement will continue unabated. “We still have 35 persons of interest who returned from impacted areas with community transmission before the border closure under our surveillance. We will continue to monitor them and give you updates as events unfold.” ”Copyright PUNCH.
